<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN212-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai – atu. tuṟai – iyaṉmoḻi. kōpperuñcōḻaṉaip piricāntaiyār pāṭiyatu.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
  </div>
    <div xml:id="PN212">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>nuṅkō yāreṉa viṉavi ṉeṅkōk</l>
<l>kaḷamark karitta viḷaiyal veṅkaḷ</l>
<l>yāmaip puḻukkiṟ kāmam vīṭa vārā</l>
<l>vāraṟ koḻuñcū ṭaṅkavu ḷaṭāa</l>
<l>vaikutoḻiṉ maṭiyu maṭiyā viḻaviṉ</l>
<l>yāṇar naṉṉāṭ ṭuḷḷum pāṇar</l>
<l>paitaṟ cuṟṟattup pacippakai yākik</l>
<l>kōḻi yōṉē kōpperuñ cōḻaṉ</l>
<l>potti ṉaṇpiṟ pottiyoṭu keḻīi</l>
<l>vāyār perunakai vaikalu nakkē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>  If you ask “who is your king?”, our king (1)</l>
<l>  is the one from Kōḻi, Kōpperum Cōḻaṉ, (8)</l>
<l>  being an enemy to the hunger of the suffering retinue (7)</l>
<l>  of bards in all [his] fertile good land (6)</l>
<l>  with festivals do not droop while the ongoing tasks droop, (5)</l>
<l>  cooking pretty cheeks of fat Āral roast, (4)</l>
<l>  not being satiated so that passion dies along with the cooked [meat] of tortoise (3)</l>
<l>  [and] ripe hot toddy that is filtered for the husbandmen, (2)</l>
<l>  – united with Potti in a friendship without hollowness, (9)</l>
<l>  smiling daily a big smile with [his] full mouth. (10)  </l>
</lg>
    </div>
